  "text": "Heavy elements ranging from 49 In to 79 Au were examined. The f (0) value was tentatively fixed to be 0.48 1/cm (≈ 1000 Hounsfield unit (HU)) in the present study. The detailed input data for the exact solutions were as follows. The radius of the phantom, R, was 0.9 cm, N = 100, and the X-ray source spectrum was for the 100 kV acceleration, which was the same as the simulation in Sec. 3.1. We obeyed Nakashima and Nakano [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] for the estimation of the bulk density of the mixture, which was needed for the LAC spectrum calculation. An example for the calculated LAC spectrum is shown in Fig. 2a for the samarium-water mixture system.",
